Also we ordered one of the specials of the day and the pork was very dry and it also tasted very old. None of the dishes were good or fresh. Luckily the only thing that was edible was a burrito we ordered for my kid everything else was dry and old and not fresh at all. Also when we sended the food back the waitress had a nasty attitude and, they wanted us to pay for disgusting food, i think if you went out to eat it is to enjoy the food or at least it has to be edible. Really bad experience. We wont ever come back. These people really need to rethink and analyze what they're serving people and do something positive about it.

Finally decided to try this hole-in-the-wall neighborhood restaurant after getting take out lots of times - and I'm so happy I did. The take out is good but the restaurant itself is amazing! The food is delicious and the portions are huge for reasonable prices.  The nachos were so good!  I will definitely be back.
Fantastic Mexican place. Probably the best plate of nachos I've ever had! All the portions are generous and at a fair price. Will be coming back for sure!

Authentic Mexican food in the Heights.  When you enter a Mexican restaurant and none of the employees speak English, you know the food is authentic.  When you dont know what the name of the restaurant means, you know the food is authentic.  The guacamole was delicious. I asked for medium spicey and it came not at all spicey.  The green sauce in the enchiladas was definitely spicey. I ordered a large Jamaica drink and it came HUGE!
Wonderful place to eat great portions great staff and amazing environment
